					<h3 class="card-title about-w3ls-page font-weight-bold text-dark pb-3 ">Equity</h3>
					<p class="card-text font-weight-normal paragraphf text-dark"align="justify"><font color="black">Equity fund is a type of mutual fund that invests in stocks. Equity represents ownership in the company(that has issued the shares) to the extent of shares held. Shareholders participate in the management of the company by exercising the voting rights associated with the shares held.They also participate n the residual profits of the company i.e the profits remaining after all the dues and claims against the company have been met,in the form of dividends.Investors benefit from high dividends that may be paid to them,as their is no assurance of the dividend or the amount of dividend.They also benefit from the appreciation in the shares.These funds also known as stock funds,are principally categorized according to company size, the investment style of the holdings in the portfolio and geography.It is investment in a growth-oriented asset.
Equity stocks may be segmented based on market capitalization as large-cap,mid-cap and small-cap stocks.
</p></font>
