					<h3 class="card-title about-w3ls-page font-weight-bold text-dark pb-3 ">Public Provident Fund(PPF)</h3>
							<p class="paragraphf text-dark"align="justify"><font color="black">PPF or Public Provident Fund is a savings scheme offered by the Government of India. The interest on the account is paid by the government of India and set every quarter. It is also tax-free.The principal and interest in the PPF account are guaranteed by the Government.Contributions to the account up to Rs 1.5 lakh per annum are tax-free. Interest on the PPF account is also tax-free.Interest Rate for the PPF account is declared by the Government every quarter. PPF returns are higher than FD rates of many banks in that period.PF accounts can also be opened by parents for their minor children.The facility to avail loan against the PPF account is available from a 3rd financial year up to 6th financial year from the date of account opening.
